Arg. II. If God does not foreknow the volitions of 
moral agents, then he did not foreknow the fall of man, 
nor of angels, and so could not foreknow the ^reat things 
which are comequevU on these events ; such* as his send* 
ing his Son into the wofid to die for sinners, and all things 
