symbolical representation ; I say, all these promises imply, 
that the Messiah should perfect the work of redemption ; 
and this implies that he. should persevere in the work 
which the Father had appointed him, being in all things 
conformed to his will. These promises were often con- 
firmed by an oath. (See Isai. liv. 9, with the context; 
