convenient." 

It is needless to stand particularly to inquire what 
God's giving men up to their own hearts^ lusts signifies : 
it is sufficient to observe, that hereby is certainly meant 
God's so Qi'dering or disposing things, in some respect or 
other, either by doing or ibrbearing to do, as that the con- 
sequence sliould be men's continuing in their sins. So 
much as men are given up to, so much is the consequence 

