etc. lead bim toto another great inconsistence. He abiin^ 
dantly insists, that necessity is incoiyistent with the na*^ 
tuire of sin or faalt. He says, in the fore-mentioned trea** 
tise, p. 14, Who can blame a person for doing what he 
eotUd not help 1 And page 15, It being sensibly unjust 
to punish any man for doing that which was net>tr in 
his power to avoid. And in p. 341, to confirm his opin* 
