enable men to perform the sincere obedience of the new 
law. ^' I grant (says Dr. Stebbing**) indeed, that by reason 
of original sin, we are utterly disabled ibr the performance 
of tbe condition, without new grace from God. But I 
say tlien, that be gives such a grace to all of us, by which 
