God doth berein is holy, and a glorious exercise of the in- 
finite excellency of his nature. And I do not deny, that 
God's being thus the author of sin follows from what I 
have laid down ; and 1 assert, that it equally follows from 
the doctrine which is maintained by most of the Arminian 
divines. 

