It is easy to see how the decision of most of the points 
in controversy betweea Calvtnists and Arminians depends 
on the determination of this grand article concerning the 
freedom of tjit will requisite to moral agency ; and that 
by clearing and establishing the Calvinistic doctrine in 
this point, the chief arguments are obviated by which 
Arminiah doctrines in general are supported, and the con- 
trary doctrines in general are demonstratively conOrmed. 
